      "Eye conditions — Collie eye anomaly (CEA), progressive retinal atrophy (PRA), iris coloboma, and cataracts all over-represented. Annual ACVO eye exam from puppyhood is the standard recommendation; many conditions are visible at the 6-week puppy exam.",
      "Hereditary cataracts — autosomal dominant in many lines; can present as young as 1-2 years.",
      "Hypothyroidism — common in middle age.",
      "Hemangiosarcoma + lymphoma — over-represented in older Aussies; monthly lump-checks plus FNA biopsy of new masses.",
      "Double-merle coat genetics — breeding two merle Aussies produces puppies with high rates of deafness, blindness, and structural abnormalities. Reputable breeders never breed merle-to-merle.",
