      "If your Scottish Fold stops jumping to high places, has changed grooming patterns (matted spots they can't reach), or seems stiff in the morning — that's progressing osteochondrodysplasia. Talk to the vet about chronic NSAIDs (cat-safe), joint supplements (omega-3s, glucosamine), and a multi-modal pain plan.",
